(9, '2020-08-28 13:37:27', '2020-09-02 18:57:47', 'CENTER FOR FORENSIC EXPERTISE', '<p>- performance of forensic expertizes and researches;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- improvement of research methods and techniques in various fields of knowledge;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- educational and methodological activities related to improvement of training and advanced training process of the specialists in the field of forensic expert activity;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- provision of commercial legal services not related to advocacy;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- development and implementation of scientific, technical and educational programs and projects;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- organization and holding of congresses, conferences, symposia, seminars, &quot;round tables&quot;;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- interaction with government and non- government agencies and organizations of the Republic of Kazakhstan and foreign countries.</p>\r\n', '5e5f59e8cd0e0d41e5e1981563bc4696.jpg', '<p>The history of origin, formation and development of the Center for Forensic Expertise of the Ministry of Justice of the Republic of Kazakhstan dates back to April 1951, when the Alma-Ata Scientific and Research Criminalistics Laboratory was founded under the Legal Commission of the Council of Ministers of the Kazakh SSR.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In April 1957, the Alma-Ata laboratory was transformed into the Alma-Ata Scientific and Research Institute of Forensic Expertise of the Ministry of Justice of the Kazakh SSR, which, by the time of its foundation, was the third forensic institute in the USSR.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Establishment of the Alma-Ata Scientific and Research Institute of Forensic Expertise marked the beginning of the development of the scientific field of forensic</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The results of the scientific and practical activities of the Alma-Ata NIISE (Scientific and Research Institute of Forensic Expertise), achievements in the development of the fundamentals of forensic expertise naturally led to transformation &nbsp;of the Alma-Ata NIISE into the Kazakh Scientific and Research Institute of Forensic Expertise by the resolution of the Council of Ministers of the Kazakh SSR dated September 8, 1966, employees which fulfilled the need for expert studies of courts and law enforcement agencies throughout the Republic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since 1975, the field of expert preventive work gained development at the Institute and the structure of the Kazakh NIISE has been changed. Besides the central office located in Alma-Ata consisting of 6 departments, from 1975 from 1975 to 1978, 10 regional units were established.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The beginning of the 90s was characterized by strengthening of the scientific field of Kaz NIISE. The activities of the Institute as a whole were repeatedly highly evaluated both by the Ministry of Justice of the USSR and other expert institutions of the Union. The positive experience of the Kazakh NIISE was spread throughout the entire system of forensic institutions of the USSR Ministry of Justice. In 1989, postgraduate training program was established at NIISE and a Specialized Council for Ph.D. defense was established.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From 1989 to 1995, 12 people defended their dissertations in the Specialized Council of the Kazakh NIISE, along with employees of the Institute there were employees of law enforcement agencies and universities of the Republic.</p>\r\n', 'Center for Forensic Expertise', NULL, '', '', '');
